{"questionId":"9900","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The number of brown squirrels, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> , in an area of woodland can be modelled by the following&nbsp;differential equation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = \\frac{x}{{1000}}\\left( {2000 - x} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2000</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x > 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Explain why the population of squirrels is increasing for values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span> less than&nbsp;this value.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>because the value of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}}\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mtext>d</mtext> </mrow> <mi>t</mi> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span> is positive (for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x > 0\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>&gt;</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9900","referenceCode":"SPM.3.AHL.TZ0.2a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Explain why the population of squirrels is increasing for values of x less than this value.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.16—Eulers method for 1st order DEs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}